  "texts": [
    "The model then predicts the most likely word to fill the [MASK] based on the context.",
    "MEM-KGC (Choi et al., 2021) adopts this process by masking the tail entity and using the head entity and relation as context to predict the missing tail entity.",
    "This is similar to MLM, where the model predicts the masked tokens based on the given context.",
    "Building on this, Choi and Ko (2023) predict the appropriate entity or relation for the masked positions.",
    "Additionally, to address the issue of new entities in open-world KGC, Choi and Ko (2023) propose a unified learning method that generates embeddings to replace token embeddings for new entities."
  ],
